<dl id="n36048e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36048e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36048e"> 48(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sign of the hammer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;The king then took the drinking horn and made the sign of the cross over it. What does the king mean? said Kaare of Gryting&rdquo;&mdash;Earl Sigurd replied&mdash;&ldquo;He is blessing the full goblet in the name of Thor by making <mark>the sign of his hammer</mark> over it.&rdquo; <small> Charles Haliday, <a name="SKD5" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SKD5"><cite title="source">The Scandinavian Kingdom of Dublin</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1884) 125n6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09037b" href="c09all.htm#c09037b">VI.C.09:037(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
